+# Memory-Optimized Build Instructions
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+1. **Rebuild FLTK without Xft support:**
+
+```bash
+# Download FLTK source
+wget https://www.fltk.org/pub/fltk/1.3.8/fltk-1.3.8-source.tar.gz
+tar xzf fltk-1.3.8-source.tar.gz
+cd fltk-1.3.8
+
+# Configure without Xft
+./configure --disable-xft --disable-xdbe --disable-xinerama --enable-shared
+make
+sudo make install
+```
+
+2. **Install unifont for Unicode support:**
+
+```bash
+sudo apt-get install xfonts-unifont
+xset fp rehash  # Refresh font path
+```
+
+## Building leafpad_fltk
+
+```bash
+make clean
+make
+```
+
+## Expected Memory Savings
+
+- **Before:** ~15-25MB RSS (with Xft/fontconfig/FreeType)
+- **After:** ~8-12MB RSS (X11 core fonts only)
+- **Savings:** ~7-13MB RSS reduction
+
+## Trade-offs
+
+- No anti-aliasing (bitmap fonts only)
+- Fixed font sizes (not smoothly scalable)
+- Basic but functional Unicode support with unifont
+
+## Troubleshooting
+
+If text doesn't display:
+1. Verify unifont is installed: `xlsfonts | grep unifont`
+2. Check available fixed fonts: `xlsfonts | grep fixed`
+3. Try setting explicit font in code (see main.cpp comments)
